article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 78, Stetson 66
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- Garrius Holloman's 14 points led five Bethune-Cookman players in double figures as the Wildcats topped cross-county rival Stetson University 78-66 on Tuesday night. C.J. Reed and Stanley Elliott contributed 13 points apiece, with Javoris Bryant and Mikel Trapp producing 11 each for Bethune-Cookman (2-0), which had not won its first two games to start a season since 1998-99. Stetson (1-1), which had opened last week with an upset win at Wake Forest, got 16 points from Ridge Graham and 12 from Tyshawn Patterson. The Hatters committed 21 turnovers to only eight for Bethune-Cookman. The Wildcats, who led 29-27 at halftime, gradually expanded the margin during the second half. The difference grew to 17 points, 62-45, when Holloman drove for an inside basket with 6:45 remaining. The lead was 17 on five occasions. Stetson could get no closer than 12 after that. The Hatters jumped to a 6-1 lead before Holloman's back-to-back baskets fueled an 8-0 Bethune-Cookman run that produced a 9-6 Wildcat lead. Bethune-Cookman never trailed the remainder of the half, once leading by seven at 8:25 on a basket by Reed. Stetson used a couple of 3-pointers by Graham to close the gap, getting it to 27-all when Steve Forbes sank a free throw at 1:52. Reed's basket 56.2 seconds before intermission provided Bethune-Cookman's halftime edge.
